text: A Texas father of two, 27-year-old Julian Ryan, died while trying to save his family from the devastating floods—nearly severing his arm as he punched through a window while the water levels rose rapidly around them. His final words: “I’m sorry, I’m not going to make it. I love y’all.”
user_description: Breaking news, features and more from the NY Post.

text:
She waited 63 years.
Clara Gantt never gave up hope that her husband, U.S. Army Sgt. 1st Class Joseph Gantt, would come home. He was captured during the Korean War and declared MIA but his remains weren't identified until 2013. In her 90s, Clara stood tall as his flag draped casket was finally returned. She never remarried.
